<PageLayout
  title="Therapeutics & the frontier"
  kicker="Pharmacology"
  description="Three melanocortin agents are FDA-approved, each exploiting a different receptor in a different organ. A broader frontier — oral agonists, biased ligands, anti-inflammatory uses — is in trials."
  updated="2026"
>
  <p>
    For decades the melanocortin system was a topic for physiology textbooks, not
    pharmacies. That has changed. Three agents are now approved, and what unites
    them is instructive: each targets a <em>different</em> receptor to treat a
    <em>different</em> disease, a direct demonstration that the same peptide family
    is reused across organs. The receptor pages explain the biology each one
    exploits — <a href="/receptors/mc4r">MC4R</a>,
    <a href="/receptors/mc1r">MC1R</a>, and the wider
    <a href="/system">system</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="not-prose mt-6 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-[var(--border)]">
    <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
      <thead class="bg-[var(--bg-elevated)] text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--text-muted)]">
